      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Electronic Fishbowl</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bed-and-breakfast operator Larry Miller letter on Marshall Sella's May 21 article holds people do not want to see strangers' living habits up close and personal</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A propos of your article, I run a bed-and-breakfast. Trust me, you don't want to see strangers' living habits up close and personal if you don't have to.</p>
        <p>Larry Miller</p>
        <p>Fleischmanns, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
